Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper focuses on the calibration of elastostatic parameters of spatial anthropomorphic robots, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
2. cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering) - The paper deals with the calibration of stiffness parameters of a manipulator with rigid links and compliant actuated joints, which is a mechanical engineering problem. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new strategy for optimal selection of measurement configurations, which is a control problem. 
4. cs.ROB (Robotics) - The paper deals with the calibration of anthropomorphic manipulators, which is a sub-domain of robotics. 
5. cs.EM (Engineering Mathematics) - The paper involves mathematical modeling and optimization of measurement configurations, which falls under the domain of engineering mathematics.
